{
	"VersionNumber": 1,
	"ResourceName": "duo_eventTypes",
	"Description": "This is intended to be used as a lookup file providing additional information regarding Duo event types. It is used within the Duo Kit for dashboards, macros, scheduled searches, alerts, flows, and templates.\n\nfields:\ntag,log_source,category,subcategory,preEVX,evx,value,description,is_mod\n  - tag: this is the associated tag to log_source\n  - log_source: this is the associated log source found in the references\n  - category: this is the category of the eventType\n  - subcategory: this is the subcategory within the category for the eventType\n  - preEVX: this is the path of the extraction for evx (e.g. action.name)\n  - evx: this is the renamed Enumerated Value from preEVX (e.g. action.name becomes actionName for Activity Logs)\n  - value: this is the value found within your logs and at the references below in the response format tables\n  - description: this will give you more information about the eventType\n  - is_mod: this field displays whether the field is a known modification eventType\n\nReference(s): \n- Duo - https://duo.com/docs/adminapi \n- Duo Activity Logs - https://duo.com/docs/adminapi#activity-logs\n- Duo Administrator Logs - https://duo.com/docs/adminapi#administrator-logs\n- Duo Authentication Logs - https://duo.com/docs/adminapi#authentication-logs\n- Duo Offline Enrollment Logs - https://duo.com/docs/adminapi#offline-enrollment-logs\n- Duo Telephony Logs - https://duo.com/docs/adminapi#telephony-logs\n\nUsage: | lookup -r duo_eventTypes eventType value (tag log_source category subcategory preEVX evx value description is_mod)",
	"Labels": [
		"duo"
	],
